   Top Corner


   The Environmental Science Group (EES-15) performs fundamental research
   on abiotic and biotic land surface processes using experiments and
   modeling to understand and mitigate risks to human health and the
   environment.

                               Horizontal Line


   Capabilities
   Our capabilities include ecological risk assessment, site remediation
   technology, surface and soil water hydrology, ecology of semiarid
   woodlands and forests, and geochemistry.

   Programs/Projects
   Our programs/projects include Environmental Restoration, Department of
   Defense (DOD), Hanford, Long-Term Risk from Actinides in the
   Environment (EMSP) and others.

   Publications
   Search our interactive database of group publications.

   Directory
   Find contact information about the current EES-15 workforce, including
   contractors.

